name: hydrocarbons purification, molecular sieve separation of naphthaÂ  | fraction 7 from naphtha separation | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/1182/documentation

The multioutput-process "naphta, to melecular sieve separations" delivers the co-products hexane, heptane, 2,3-dimethylbutane, 2-methylpentane, methylcyclopentane, 1,1-dimethylcyclopentane, methylcyclohexane, fraction 1 from naphta, fraction 7 from naphta, and fraction 8 from naphta. The allocation is based on mass balance.



Molecular sieve separation of naphta including materials, energy uses, infrastructure and emissions.
category: C:Manufacturing/19:Manufacture of coke and refined petroleum products/192:Manufacture of refined petroleum products/1920:Manufacture of refined petroleum products

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: The inventory is modelled with data from plants in the USA.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Separation of naphta with a zeolith 5a molecular sieve.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: This dataset has been extrapolated from european data. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly. Some data are derived from other or unknown plants or have been estimated.
